OVERVIEW

VIVOS corpus is a free Vietnamese speech corpus consisting of 15 hours of recording speech. The corpus is prepared for Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) task and explicitly divided into training and testing set.

The corpus was prepared by AILAB, a computer science lab of VNUHCM - University of Science, with Prof. Vu Hai Quan is the head of.

Speech was recorded in a quite enviroment with high quality microphones, speakers were asked to read a pre-prepared text line by line.


